content.description: Fun little roof to climb through. Look for the foot options, the bolts are close enough together to calm your head; no need to cry.

Start the route on a small sketchy looking flake and reach out to a good pinch and a bad crimp find some feet and move up to the good holds by the 2nd bolt.  The last part of the crux involves a balancy perch on the pinch, if one were to fall here, I'm not sure if the first bolt would prevent a ground fall.  After the second bolt the climbing eases up substantially past another 2 bolts to the top.  Note this climb will feel easier the taller you are, if you're short the crux will feel quite hard, if you're tall you could reach through some of the difficulty making it feel easier than the stated grade.
content.protection: 4 Bolts to rap hangers.  I recommend stick clipping the second bolt to prevent a potential ground fall.
content.location: The overgrown route to the left of 9 if by left.

content.description: Climb the corner between the flat wall and the steep blocky over hanging route. Maybe you can sneak over and TR Click,Click, Boom

This route shares the first 3 bolts of 9 If by Left, then rather than trending left, continue straight up the overhanging face/corner using some cool corner climbing.  The crux is at the 2nd last bolt going from the undercling to a good jug.  Due to the grunge, getting to the anchors could be quite cruxy as well.  Ends at a 2 shut anchor
content.location: Last route on the mid-wall in a left facing corner to the left of a seeping wall.
